oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Home Canning, Preserving, and Pickling
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Fifty-seven page typed booklet titled, "Home Canning, Preserving, and Pickling" published by the Agricultural Extension Service from the University of Tennessee at Knoxville. The booklet provides instructions on canning and pickling methods for various types of food such as butter, fruits, vegetables, jelly, meats, pickles, eggs, etc. The booklet was compiled and adapted by Maude Guthrie, a food and nutrition specialist.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Guthrie, Maude
